title: Jose Estradas’s CV
text: Finance and Economy focusing in Financial Analyst on Private Equity

title: Jose Estradas’s CV
text:
KEY SKILLS AND CERTIFICATES

Business Intelligence & Visualization: Power BI, Microsoft Excel, Tableau
Participated in the CFA Institute Research Challenge, conducted the valuation, and equity research on a
publicly traded company
Financial Modeling and Forecasting Financial Statements Certificate
Programming & Data Management: R, SQL (MySQL, Statistical & Data Analysis)
Participant, Bloomberg Global Trading Challenge, collaborated as a team leader of five to supervise a virtual
investment portfolio of $1M in a global competitive environment
Bloomberg Market Concepts Certificate


Experience
Teaching Assistant
Brigham Young University–Idaho, Department of Economics
Rexburg, ID | August 2022 – Present
- Reviewed weekly performance of 90+ students across multiple sections, implementing targeted teaching strategies.
- Coordinated a team of TAs in designing and executing feedback systems, significantly boosting teaching outcomes.
Finance Intern
The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints
Salt Lake City, UT | April 2024 – September 2024
- Analyzed 25,000+ properties across the U.S. using Power BI to support data-driven decision-making.
- Corrected over 5,000 property record errors using advanced Excel data validation techniques to improve accuracy and reliability.
CPA Assistant
Contadores Fiscales Especializados, E.G
Chiapas, Mexico | January 2020 – February 2021
- Maintained financial records by processing 500+ journal entries with Conta Fiscal software.
- Organized and updated balance sheets, income statements, and accounting records to ensure audit readiness. ““”


Projects
Financial Analysis Project
- Analyzed Weighted Average Cost of Capital (WACC) trends, identifying a 5.9% hurdle rate optimal for capital budgeting.
- Informed leadership on investment risk and return expectations to support strategic decision-making.
- Streamlined financial comparisons across top firms using Excel and Bloomberg to clarify market positioning and enhance financial strategy.
Investment Portfolio Analysis (Power BI)
- Developed an interactive Power BI dashboard analyzing 1,000+ ETFs, indexes, and mutual funds to identify optimal portfolio combinations.
- Extracted and integrated financial data from Morningstar and Yahoo Finance, including yield and risk metrics.
- Supported fund performance analysis and portfolio optimization through data-driven insights. ““”
